This assignment uses python scripts to compare AWS and Azure products.
In particular I explore Amazon S3 and DynamoDB, and Azure Blob Storage
along with CosmosDB.


Setup
-----
    - Install virtual environment creator and package manager package 
      pipenv:

      pip install pipenv

    - Install all project dependencies:

      pipenv install

    - Configure ~/.aws/credentials file with your access token

    - Set AZURE_STORAGE_CONNECTION_STRING environment variable with your
      blob storage connection string.

    - Change database connection string in config.py to your cosmosDB 
      instance.

Usage
-----
    - S3 Data Loader:
    pipenv run python3 createPopContainersAWS.py
    pipenv run python3 createPopContainersAWS.py reset //for teardown
    
    - Blob Storage Loader:
    pipenv run python3 createPopContainersAzure.py
    pipenv run python3 createPopContainersAzure.py reset //for teardown

    - S3 Client Program:
    pipenv run python3 storageApplianceAWS.py

    - Blob Storage Client Program:
    pipenv run python3 storageApplianceAzure.py

    - DynamoDB Data Loader:
    pipenv run python3 createMovieDBAWS.py

    - Azure CosmosDB Data Loader:
    pipenv run python3 createMovieDBAzure.py

    - DynamoDB Client Program:
    pipenv run python3 queryDBAWS.py

    - Azure CosmosDB Client Program (IN PROGRESS):
    pipenv run python3 queryDBAzure.py

Notes
-----
    - Dynamo Client:
    By default the projected attributes are year, title, and 
    info.rating. User can add more but can't take these away.
